definition: (coll.) likelihood of being worthwhile/cf. 有搞頭|有搞头[you3 gao3 tou5] and 沒搞頭|没搞头[mei2 gao3 tou5]
to do/to make/to go in for/to set up/to get hold of/to take care of

sentences.english: He spent an unprofitable year abroad.
sentences.chinese: 他在國外度過沒有搞頭一年。

sentences.english: Keep smiling, it makes people wonder what you're up to.
